dino (1.1.2.8) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Legacy Encryption Format Fallback: decrypt_data() auto-falls back to
    pre-v1.1.2.7 encryption format (SALT=8, IV=16, TAG=8). Old avatars
    silently re-encrypted to current format on first access.
  * Avatar Decrypt Retry Spam: failed_decrypt_hashes prevents repeated
    expensive PBKDF2 (~100ms each) for corrupt/legacy files.
  * store_image() pre-populates avatar bytes cache for instant access.
  * Recommendation: Panic Wipe (Ctrl+Shift+Alt+P) for cleanest migration
    to new encryption parameters, or let auto-migration handle it.

