dino (1.1.0.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Botmother Phase 3: AI, Telegram, TLS, OpenClaw
  * AI Integration: 9 providers (OpenAI, Claude, Gemini, Groq, Mistral,
    DeepSeek, Perplexity, Ollama, OpenClaw) with per-bot config, conversation
    history, system prompts, and interactive /ki menu system
  * OpenClaw: Added as 9th AI provider -- autonomous agent/orchestrator
    via webhook API (POST /hooks/agent), not a passive LLM but an active
    agent that manages multiple AI models internally
  * Telegram Bridge: Bidirectional message bridging (XMPP <-> Telegram),
    bridge/forward modes, long-poll message ingestion, /telegram menu
  * HTTP API: Telegram endpoints (setup, status, enable, send, test),
    AI endpoints (setup, status, enable, ask), total 31 REST endpoints
  * TLS/API Server: Network mode with auto-generated self-signed certs
    (GnuTLS cert_gen.c), custom PEM cert support, /api server commands
  * Auto-restart: API server restarts automatically on settings change
    (mode, port, cert, key) with 500ms debounce -- no manual restart needed
  * Dedicated Bot Mode: Own XMPP account via ejabberd API, automatic OMEMO
    key generation, owner-only binding, presence subscription, bot_password
    in DB schema v3
  * Bot OMEMO: Automatic OMEMO v1/v2 key generation and session management
    for dedicated bots, encrypted bot-owner conversations
  * Session Pool: Dedicated XMPP stream management, auto-reconnect,
    per-bot stream isolation
  * Interactive Menus: /help, /ki, /telegram, /api command trees with
    in-chat documentation and examples
  * i18n: All user-facing strings use _() for translation readiness
  * Preferences UI: Botmother section with API mode, port, TLS cert
    management, ejabberd settings panel
  * Documentation: API_BOTMOTHER_AI_GUIDE.md (2300+ lines, 12 chapters)

 -- Dino Developers <chat@dino.im>  Sun, 15 Feb 2026 12:00:00 +0000

